{"type":"message","id":"1170be07","parentId":"dcd5acd3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:44:49.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. The `control_tower_payload` comes from loading a previously generated control tower JSON file. The health check reads from `control_tower_{tag}.json` (line 67 of generate_investment_research_mainline_health.py). \n\nThe issue is:\n1. Today's control tower file (`control_tower_20260324.json`) doesn't exist yet\n2. The health check tries to load it and gets nothing\n3. All fields become `None`\n4. All checks fail → ALERT\n\nThis is expected because the cron jobs haven't run yet today. The `NEWS_MARKET_0850` runs at 08:50, `INVESTMENT_RESEARCH_BRIEF_MORNING` at 08:30, `RESEARCH_BUNDLE_MORNING` at 09:32, etc.\n\n\nSince it's currently 04:43 AM, these scheduled jobs haven't executed yet. The ALERT status makes sense given the early timing, but I should determine if any of the missing components can be generated now. The news-market cron at 08:50 is the first one that could run, followed by the investment research brief at 08:30.\n\nLooking at the other scheduled tasks—the bundle generation at 09:32 and mainline guard at 09:34—none of them can execute right now since we're not at their scheduled times. This is a normal pre-market state where the system is waiting for the trading day to begin.\n\nSince the ALERT is just reflecting that today's cron jobs haven't run yet, I should document this finding and then spawn a subagent to handle the continuous monitoring and any preparatory work that can be done in advance, while I also run through the self-improvement checklist since it's morning.","thinkingSignature":"498d39a35908fc9cb5feb02321a63dd96bc67e4c050db9ef1c57b68b903e716a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_suxu3xn4s7vi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/ | grep -E \"control_tower.*2026032[123]\" | sort"}},{"type":"toolCall","i