{"type":"message","id":"8ebfc7d3","parentId":"5a1f6f38","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:21:14.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The premarket precheck for today (20260324) is missing - only 20260323 exists. This is a problem! The premarket precheck did NOT run for today (20260324). \n\nAccording to the rules:\n- \"Trading-day Premarket Precheck (09:20-09:40)\": \"失败时主动汇报阻断原因与报告路径\"\n\nBut wait - the precheck is supposed to run automatically via cron. Let me check if there's a cron job for it and if it ran today. Also, the heartbeat said the precheck status was \"blocked\" in the strategy audit. This could mean the precheck was blocked.\n\n\nNow I need to figure out whether the cron job failed to trigger or if it ran but produced no output - either way, I need to report this gap since today was a trading day and the precheck should have completed during the 09:20-09:40 window. I'm checking the cron logs to see if the precheck ran today or if something failed silently—the missing 20260324 file is a red flag since the 20260323 version exists, suggesting the scheduled task either didn't trigger or hit an error. is missing.\n\nWait - but the USER.md says \"盘前强检由助手自动执行，失败要主动汇报阻断原因\". So I should report that the precheck for today didn't run.\n\nBut actually, looking at this more carefully - the cron job is `30 09 * * 1-5` for `run_investment_research_org_publish_bundle.py`. Let me check if there's a separate cron for `auto_run_premarket_precheck.py`.\n\nThe checklist says: `cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/auto_run_premarket_precheck.py`\n\nBut I don't see this in the crontab output from earlier. Let me check the crontab for this script specifically.\n\nSince the precheck report for today is missing and it's already past the 09:20-09:40 window, I should run it manually to fill the gap and report the results.","thinkingSignature":"4ed56f1a7a1a77fdfb391c437a9727f7bc41ad1368915f