{"type":"message","id":"7feb9e14","parentId":"29670c33","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:22:32.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The precheck ran with `--force` but hit a blocking error: the `run_live_execution_v1.py` script requires `--trading-mode live` to be explicitly set. This is a configuration issue - the precheck is trying to run live execution but the trading mode isn't set properly.\n\nLooking at the output:\n- `status: \"blocked\"` - it's blocked\n- The error is: `ValueError: 必须显式设置 TRADING_MODE=live 或传入 --trading-mode live`\n- The precheck did generate a report file: `auto_premarket_precheck_20260324.json`\n\nNow, the question is: is this the reason the cron job didn't run today? But wait - the cron job doesn't exist at all. \n\nSo the cron for this script is missing entirely, but when I ran it manually with `--force` it still failed due to that trading mode error. The underlying issue is that the script requires either the environment variable or the flag to be set, and that's preventing the precheck from running even when forced. I should report the missing cron to Zhang Ling along with this trading mode configuration problem. Let me check the generated report file and then report.","thinkingSignature":"ae4850f2c84298bf84502b044b44309701bb7f12cc1ed317cc2e0cb540d31b8f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qsd7gdw51ly3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/auto_premarket_precheck_20260324.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:d[k] for k in ['status','status_reason','date','passed','strict_precheck','hard_stop','halt_reason','report_file']}, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\"","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qsd7gdw51ly3_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"TRADING_MODE\\|trading-mode\\|trading_mode\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quan